    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nI tried to use neovim as MANPAGER and it correctly parses and displays manpages. There is no problem. But when I try to use this instance of neovim to open more manpages via `K` shortcut or `:Man` command, it cannot find any manpage. Shows me error message of `man -w`. When I try command `:!man -w` it only shows first entry on the **MANPATH**. Note that it also modifies MANPATH.\n\nNote: I tried it again and now it shows another single entry. It finds manpages where them exist in this directory.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n```\nexport MANPATH=\":$HOME/.local/share/man:$HOME/share/man\"\nexport MANPAGER=\"nvim +Man!\"\nman read\n# then try to open another manpage within neovim, even same page will not open\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nShould work same as opening neovim normally and using `:Man` command. And it should not edit MANPATH before calling `man -w`.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.12.2\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nI did not try it.\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nvoid linux (rolling release)\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nfoot 1.27.0\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nfoot\n\n### Installation\n\nsystem package manager",
