            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "> Works for me on bash. Try this\n> \n> In your .bashrc\n> \n> export MANPATH=\"$(manpath -g):/opt/sw/neovim/share/man\"\n> In your init.lua\n> \n> vim.opt.shell = \"bash\"\n> vim.opt.shellcmdflag = \"-c\"\n> Verify in neovim:\n> \n> :! echo $0  \"bash\n> :! echo $MANPATH \"should be there\n\nYes, this should help. Since man itself destroys MANPATH, rebuilding it before executing man should solve issue.",
